    "claim": "`transferTokenToOrderbook` decreases `pool.totalToken`/`pool.totalLiquidity` by the requested `amount`, and `receiveTokenFromOrderbook` later increases them by the requested `amount`, but neither function measures the pool's actual token balance delta. If the listed asset charges transfer fees, burns on transfer, or otherwise confiscates part of the amount, every orderbook borrow/repay cycle can silently destroy pool assets while internal accounting still assumes the full amount moved.",
    "impact": "A pool can become progressively undercollateralized through normal orderbook activity even when LP deposits were correct. Once the hidden deficit grows large enough, LP withdrawals or later orderbook settlements revert because the contract no longer holds the recorded number of tokens.",
    "paths": [
      "Orderbook borrows `amount` tokens via `transferTokenToOrderbook`; a fee-on-transfer token delivers less than `amount` to the orderbook, but the pool is debited by the full `amount` anyway.",
      "Orderbook later repays `amount` through `receiveTokenFromOrderbook`; if the token taxes or burns on inbound transfer, the pool receives less than `amount` while internal accounting credits the full `amount`.",
      "Repeated fills accumulate an invisible deficit until `safeTransfer` on LP withdrawal or later settlement fails."
    ]
